\subsection{Unit in a ring}
\begin{definition}\label{ring.unit}
\uses{group,ring}
A **unit** in a {{KNOWL('ring', 'commutative ring')}} $R$ is an element $x \in R$ so that there exists $y \in R$ with $xy = 1$.  The set of units in $R$ is denoted $R^*$ or $R^\times$ and forms a {{KNOWL('group', 'group')}} under multiplication.
\end{definition}


